data.-the-magic-zero-code-enhancement#üîç Th:
The Problem: You have a working MCP server but need to add authentication, logging, AI summarization, or monitoring. Traditional approaches require modifying your server code, adding dependencies, and maintaining complex integrations.The Solution: The proxy wrapper intercepts your server's tool registration process and transparently enhances each tool with plugin functionality, while preserving your original code completely unchanged.
// Your existing server stays exactly the same
const server = new McpServer({ name: 'My Server', version: '1.0.0' });
server.tool('getData', schema, originalHandler); // ‚Üê NO CHANGES TO THIS
// The proxy wrapper creates an enhanced version
const enhancedServer = await wrapWithProxy(server, {
  plugins: [new LLMSummarizationPlugin()]
});
// Now your tools have AI summarization without code changes!

